modules.description: This module creates an Lwt-based session manager using a provided backend, handling session retrieval, creation, modification, and expiration. It works with string keys and values, and expiration periods in seconds, tracking modifications to control cookie header output. It is used to manage user sessions via cookies in web applications, allowing operations like session initialization from HTTP headers, updating session data, and generating appropriate cookie headers for client responses.

This module implements a session management system using cookies and Lwt for asynchronous handling. It supports session creation, retrieval, and expiration using string-based keys and values, with time-to-live specified in seconds. Operations include initializing sessions from HTTP headers, updating session data, and generating cookie headers for responses. Example usage includes tracking user logins and managing session state across web requests.
